          =\frac{2.00}{6\times10^{-3}}\;\frac{\text{J}}{\text{m}^{2}\,\text{s}}
          =3.33\times10^{2}\;\frac{\text{J}}{\text{m}^{2}\,\text{s}}
          =3.33\times10^{2}\;\text{W m}^{-2}
\]

\[
\boxed{I_{\odot}=3.33\times10^{2}\;\text{W m}^{-2}}
\]

---

**2. Temperatures of the reservoirs**

\[
T_h = 79.5^{\circ}\text{C}=79.5+273.15=352.65\;\text{K}
\]
\[
T_c = 298\;\text{K}
\]

---

**3. Carnot (maximum) efficiency**

\[
\eta_{\text{Carnot}} = 1-\frac{T_c}{T_h}
                     = 1-\frac{298}{352.65}
                     = 1-0.8455
                     = 0.1545\;( \approx 15.5\% )
\]

---

**4. Heat that must be supplied to the engine**

The desired mechanical power is \(P_{\text{out}} = 1000\;\text{W}\).

\[
