#### 67.0

The spectral radiance of a black‑body per unit wavelength is  

\[
B(\lambda ,T)=\frac{2hc^{2}}{\lambda^{5}}\,
\frac{1}{\exp\!\left(\dfrac{hc}{\lambda kT}\right)-1}
\]

For a given temperature the prefactor \(2hc^{2}\) cancels when we form a ratio, so  

\[
\frac{B(\lambda_{1},T)}{B(\lambda_{2},T)}
   =\left(\frac{\lambda_{2}}{\lambda_{1}}\right)^{5}
     \frac{\exp\!\left(\dfrac{hc}{\lambda_{2}kT}\right)-1}
          {\exp\!\left(\dfrac{hc}{\lambda_{1}kT}\right)-1}.
\]

---

### 1.  Constants  

\[
\begin{aligned}
h &=6.62607015\times10^{-34}\ {\rm J\,s},\\[2pt]
c &=2.99792458\times10^{8}\ {\rm m\,s^{-1}},\\[2pt]
k &=1.380649\times10^{-23}\ {\rm J\,K^{-1}},\\[2pt]
\frac{hc}{k}&=0.01438777\ {\rm m\,K}.
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 2.  Exponential arguments  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\lambda_{1}&=450\ {\rm nm}=4.50\times10^{-7}\ {\rm m},\\
\lambda_{2}&=700\ {\rm nm}=7.00\times10^{-7}\ {\rm m},\\[4pt]
x_{1}&=\frac{hc}{\lambda_{1}kT}
      =\frac{0.01438777}{(4.50\times10^{-7})(298)}
      \approx 1.0728\times10^{2},\\[4pt]
x_{2}&=\frac{hc}{\lambda_{2}kT}
      =\frac{0.01438777}{(7.00\times10^{-7})(298)}
      \approx 6.896\times10^{1}.
\end{aligned}
\]

Both \(x_{1}\) and \(x_{2}\) are \(\gg 1\); therefore \(\exp(x)-1\approx\exp(x)\).

---

### 3.  Ratio  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\frac{B(450\ {\rm nm})}{B(700\ {\rm nm})}
&\approx\left(\frac{7.00\times10^{-7}}{4.50\times10^{-7}}\right)^{5}
   \exp\!\bigl(x_{2}-x_{1}\bigr)\\[4pt]
&=\left(\frac{700}{450}\right)^{5}
   \exp\!\bigl(-38.32\bigr)\\[4pt]
&=1.5556^{5}\times e^{-38.32}\\[4pt]
&\approx 9.10 \times 2.29\times10^{-17}\\[4pt]
&\approx 2.1\times10^{-16}.
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 4.  Result (in units of \(10^{-16}\))

\[
\boxed{\displaystyle \frac{B(450\ {\rm nm})}{B(700\ {\rm nm})}\;\approx\;2.1\times10^{-16}}
\]

Hence, the black‑body emits roughly \(2.1\) × \(10^{-16}\) times as much energy at 450 nm as at 700 nm when the temperature is \(298\ \text{K}\).  

